{
  "text": "Adult male and female carp, Cyprinus carpio L., weighing around 100 g, were obtained from the central fish culture facility ('de Haar vissen') of the Agricultural University of Wageningen, The Netherlands. The isogenic carp strains used for the experiments were E4, E4 R3R8, E20 R8 and R3 R8; wild-type carp from our laboratory stock were also used [CITATION_1] . The fish were held in 100 litre tanks with circulating, filtered and well-aerated tapwater at 24 C and a photoperiod of 16 h light alternating with 8 h darkness. The fish were fed commercial fish food (Trouvit; Trouw, Putten, The Netherlands), at a ration of 1\u00b75% of the body weight per day.",
  "citation_candidates": [
